#. [message], speaker=Celyn
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\28_Travelers.cfg:1293
msgid ""
"It iz true the banditz are uzing uz to their endz, but they never attacked "
"uz. \n"
"We are Travellerz, not barbarianz. \n"
"We try not to provoke them, and they don’t dare taking it out on uz."
msgstr ""
"Ez cierto que loz banditaz noz uzan para zuz propioz fin, pero nunca noz "
"atacaron.\n"
"Zomoz Viajeroz, no bárbaroz.\n"
"Intentamoz no provocarlez, y elloz no ze atreven a dezzaharciar con nozotroz."

#. [message], speaker=Hury
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\28_Travelers.cfg:1309
msgid ""
"Fdi is zo afflicted by the lozz of Bta that he iz not aware of the growing "
"threat that are banditz and goblinz eazt."
msgstr ""
"Fdi eztá tan afectado por la pérdidaz de Bta que no ez conziente de la "
"creciente amenaza que zon loz banditaz y goblinzez al ezte."

#. [message], speaker=unit
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\28_Travelers.cfg:1313
msgid "How are they a threat?"
msgstr "¿Cómo son una amenaza?"

#. [message], speaker=Hury
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\28_Travelers.cfg:1317
msgid ""
"We gave them too much and they want more. \n"
"If only we still had Bta and Ubidaiubua with uz, we could probably defend "
"ourzelvez, but without them, we gonna get zlaughtered."
msgstr ""
"Lez dimoz demaziado y ahora quieren máz.\n"
"Zi todavía tuviéramoz a Bta y a Ubidaiubua con nozotroz, probablemente "
"podríamoz defendernoz, pero zin ellaz, noz van a mazacrar."

#. [message], speaker=Ve
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\28_Travelers.cfg:1332
msgid ""
"It is zaid that a hero is fazing the danger of Oa’z gallery despite the "
"legion’z withdrawal. Could it be you, that grandee? "
msgstr ""
"Ze dice que un héroe eztá enfrentando el peligro de la galería de Oa a pezar "
"de la retirada de la legión. ¿Podría zer uzted ez, gran señor?"

#. [message], speaker=unit
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\28_Travelers.cfg:1336
msgid "Yes, this should be us."
msgstr "Sí, deberíamos ser nosotros."

#. [message], speaker=Ve
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\28_Travelers.cfg:1340
msgid ""
"In that case, the Black Zizter azked me to tell you about the danger that iz "
"threatening uz, but you muzt promise me not the tell a word to the women "
"from our camp."
msgstr ""
"En ese caso, la Hermana Negra me pidió que te hablara del peligro que nos "
"amenaza, pero debes prometerme que no dirás ni una palabra a las mujeres de "
"nuestro campamento."

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\28_Travelers.cfg:1344
msgid "Who is the Black Sister?"
msgstr "¿Quién es la Hermana Negra?"

#. [message], speaker=Ve
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\28_Travelers.cfg:1348
msgid "This is not relevant."
msgstr "Eso no es relevante."

#. [message], speaker=Ve
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\28_Travelers.cfg:1352
msgid ""
"In the pazt, the banditz were tolerating uz because we were zupplying them "
"but zince the legion withdrawn its troopz, the banditz who were committing "
"petty theftz and robbing caravanz are now pillaging and killing."
msgstr ""
"En el pasado, los bandidos nos toleraban porque les suministrábamos cosas, "
"pero desde que la legión retiró sus tropas, los bandidos que antes solo "
"cometían pequeños robos y asaltaban caravanas ahora saquean y matan."

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\28_Travelers.cfg:1356
msgid "This sounds quite bad."
msgstr "Eso suena bastante grave."

#. [message], speaker=Ve
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\28_Travelers.cfg:1360
msgid ""
"This morning, we found one buzy ztealing in Koezaran’s tent. He told uz that "
"the bandit leader claims the property of the women and goodz of our camp and "
"that they will come back tonight in force to help themzelvez."
msgstr ""
"Esta mañana encontramos a uno robando en la tienda de Koezaran. Nos dijo que "
"el líder de los bandidos reclama la propiedad de las mujeres y de las cosas "
"de nuestro campamento y que volverán esta noche en fuerza para apropiarse de "
"todo."

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\28_Travelers.cfg:1364
msgid "Can't you do anything to prevent that?"
msgstr "¿No pueden hacer nada para evitarlo?"

#. [message], speaker=Ve
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\28_Travelers.cfg:1368
msgid ""
"This makez me zick. The Green Mountainz are right behind uz, but we cannot "
"face Oa’s gallery without Bta’s and Ubidaiubua’s help."
msgstr ""
"Esto me enferma. Las Montañas Verdes están justo detrás de nosotros, pero no "
"podemos enfrentar la galería de Oa sin la ayuda de Bta y Ubidaiubua."

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\28_Travelers.cfg:1372
msgid ""
"I see. There are the bandits in front and the dangers of the gallery behind."
msgstr "Entiendo. Los bandidos adelante y los peligros de la galería atrás."

#. [message], speaker=Ve
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\28_Travelers.cfg:1380
msgid ""
"If you’re a true hero, you muzt be courageouz enough to fight the bandit "
"leader for uz."
msgstr ""
"Si eres un verdadero héroe, debes tener el coraje suficiente para pelear "
"contra el líder de los bandidos por nosotros."

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\28_Travelers.cfg:1384
msgid "But wha"
msgstr "Pero qué"

#. [message], speaker=Ve
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\28_Travelers.cfg:1388
msgid ""
"You won’t get any reward in return, but I would bet he amazzed a zmall "
"fortune in his bandit’z lair."
msgstr ""
"No recibirás ninguna recompensa a cambio, pero apostaría a que él acumuló "
"una pequeña fortuna en su guarida de bandidos."

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\28_Travelers.cfg:1392
msgid "So whe"
msgstr "Entonces dón"

#. [message], speaker=Ve
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\28_Travelers.cfg:1396
msgid "You muzt zwear to ztay zilent until your clash with the bandit leader."
msgstr ""
"Debes jurar que guardarás silencio hasta que te enfrentes al líder de los "
"bandidos."

#. [message], speaker=Evuyjixcih
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\28_Travelers.cfg:1410
msgid ""
"I’ll go straight to the point, my child, as I’m old and some things can’t "
"wait anymore."
msgstr ""
"Iré directo al grano, hijo mío, porque soy viejo y algunas cosas ya no "
"pueden esperar."

#. [message], speaker=unit
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\28_Travelers.cfg:1414
msgid "Tell us."
msgstr "Cuéntanos."

#. [message], speaker=Evuyjixcih
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\28_Travelers.cfg:1418
msgid "Your kingdom is dancing with evil forces."
msgstr "Tu reino está bailando con fuerzas del mal."

#. [message], speaker=unit
#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\28_Travelers.cfg:1422
#: .\scenarios\chapter6\39_Oofs_Fortress.cfg:252
#: .\scenarios\chapter6\43_Western_Village.cfg:255
msgid "What do you mean?"
msgstr "¿Qué quieres decir?"

#. [message], speaker=Evuyjixcih
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\28_Travelers.cfg:1426
msgid ""
"The current events are the harvest of what the irresponsible have sown a "
"long time ago. They touched what should have been left in peace. "
msgstr ""
"Los acontecimientos actuales son la cosecha de lo que los irresponsables "
"sembraron hace mucho tiempo. Tocaron lo que debería haberse dejado en paz."

#. [message], speaker=unit
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\28_Travelers.cfg:1430
msgid "Not helping?"
msgstr "¿No ayudar?"

#. [message], speaker=Evuyjixcih
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\28_Travelers.cfg:1434
msgid "You will need a lot of allies, but you first must save your kingdom."
msgstr "Necesitarás muchos aliados, pero primero debes salvar tu reino."

#. [message], speaker=trader
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\28_Travelers.cfg:1485
msgid "If you need potions or magic items, they are yours at low price."
msgstr "Si necesitas pociones u objetos mágicos, son tuyos a bajo precio."

#. [message], speaker=trader
#. [object]
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\28_Travelers.cfg:1545 .\utils\item_list.cfg:9472
msgid "A soul black as night"
msgstr "Un alma negra como la noche"

#. [message], speaker=trader
#. [object]
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\28_Travelers.cfg:1546 .\utils\item_list.cfg:9490
msgid "Regeneration"
msgstr "Regeneración"

#. [message], speaker=trader
#. [object]
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\28_Travelers.cfg:1547 .\utils\item_list.cfg:9506
msgid "Ice breath"
msgstr "Aliento de hielo"

#. [message], speaker=trader
#. [object]
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\28_Travelers.cfg:1548 .\utils\item_list.cfg:9612
msgid "Focused spirit"
msgstr "Espíritu enfocado"

#. [message], speaker=trader
#. [object]
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\28_Travelers.cfg:1549 .\utils\item_list.cfg:9626
msgid "To make a corpse explode"
msgstr "Para hacer explotar un cadáver"

#. [message], speaker=trader
#. [object]
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\28_Travelers.cfg:1576
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\32_Eastern_Swamp.cfg:1890
#: .\scenarios\chapter6\39_Oofs_Fortress.cfg:586 .\utils\item_list.cfg:8927
msgid "Potion of rejuvenation"
msgstr "Poción de rejuvenecimiento"

#. [message], speaker=Eukhac
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\28_Travelers.cfg:1789
msgid "I'm Eukhac, the best bowwoman of Idaamub."
msgstr "Soy Eukhac, la mejor arquera de Idaamub."

#. [message], speaker=Eukhac
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\28_Travelers.cfg:1804
msgid "I am ruined, fully ruined!"
msgstr "¡Estoy arruinada, completamente arruinada!"

#. [message], speaker=Eukhac
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\28_Travelers.cfg:1808
msgid ""
"During six years, all my money and all my efforts went into the preparation "
"of the contest of best bowman of the known lands. "
msgstr ""
"Durante seis años, todo mi dinero y todos mis esfuerzos fueron para la "
"preparación del concurso de mejor arquero de las tierras conocidas. "

#. [message], speaker=Eukhac
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\28_Travelers.cfg:1812
msgid ""
"But the day right before the contest, catastrophe! Our funds were stolen by "
"the goblins! Our prizes were stolen! "
msgstr ""
"¡Pero el día justo antes del concurso, catástrofe! ¡Nuestros fondos fueron "
"robados por los goblins! ¡Nuestros premios fueron robados! "

#. [message], speaker=Eukhac
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\28_Travelers.cfg:1816
msgid ""
"I only have my bow and my talent left to try to save my stained reputation."
msgstr ""
"Solo me queda mi arco y mi talento para intentar salvar mi reputación "
"manchada."

#. [message], speaker=Eukhac
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\28_Travelers.cfg:1820
msgid ""
"I followed the goblins down to here, but I can’t go any further as I ain’t "
"got a dime to buy food. "
msgstr ""
"Seguí a los goblins hasta aquí, pero no puedo ir más lejos ya que no tengo "
"ni un centavo para comprar comida. "

#. [message], speaker=Eukhac
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\28_Travelers.cfg:1839
msgid ""
"If you have a bit of gold for me, I would be glad to help you. That way, I "
"would continue looking for my stolen treasure in good company."
msgstr ""
"Si tienes un poco de oro para mí, estaría encantada de ayudarte. De esa "
"forma, continuaría buscando mi tesoro robado en buena compañía."

#. [message], speaker=Eukhac
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\28_Travelers.cfg:1843
msgid "I would need 38400 gold to reimburse the Travellers and buy some food."
msgstr ""
"Necesitaría 38400 oro para reembolsar a los Viajeros y comprar algo de "
"comida."

#. [message], speaker=Eukhac
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\28_Travelers.cfg:1847
msgid "Can you help me?"
msgstr "¿Puedes ayudarme?"

#. [option]
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\28_Travelers.cfg:1849
msgid "Yes, we can."
msgstr "Sí, podemos."

#. [message], speaker=Eukhac
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\28_Travelers.cfg:1859
msgid "I am afraid you don't have enough gold to help me."
msgstr "Temo que no tienes suficiente oro para ayudarme."

#. [message], speaker=Eukhac
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\28_Travelers.cfg:1903
msgid ""
"The bow and honor of Eukhac are yours, my good friend. I am glad to follow "
"you."
msgstr ""
"El arco y el honor de Eukhac son tuyos, mi buen amigo. Estoy encantada de "
"seguirte."

#. [option]
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\28_Travelers.cfg:1916
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\32_Eastern_Swamp.cfg:1164
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:873
msgid "Sorry, we don't have enough gold."
msgstr "Lo siento, no tenemos suficiente oro."

#. [message], speaker=Eukhac
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\28_Travelers.cfg:1920
msgid "Please excuse me for my straightforward request. "
msgstr "Por favor discúlpame por mi solicitud directa. "

#. [message], speaker=Eukhac
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\28_Travelers.cfg:1924
msgid "I should have seen that your funds are in the same state as mines."
msgstr ""
"Debería haber visto que tus fondos están en el mismo estado que los míos."

#. [message], speaker=Eukhac
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\28_Travelers.cfg:1928
msgid "Farewell, then, and may luck be in your favor."
msgstr "Adiós, entonces, y que la suerte esté a tu favor."

#. [scenario], id=29_Black_Forest
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\29_Black_Forest.cfg:4
msgid "Black Forest"
msgstr "Bosque Negro"

#. [objective], condition=win
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\29_Black_Forest.cfg:37
msgid "Cross the Black Forest to the Eastern Swamp"
msgstr "Cruza el Bosque Negro al Pantano Oriental"

#. [objective], condition=win
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\29_Black_Forest.cfg:42
msgid "Also kill all remaining trolls"
msgstr "También mata a todos los trolls restantes"

#. [side], type=Bandit
#. [side], type=Huntsman
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\29_Black_Forest.cfg:347
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\30_Bandit_Camp.cfg:100
msgid "Bandits"
msgstr "Bandidos"

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\29_Black_Forest.cfg:438
msgid "This forest is quite dark."
msgstr "Este bosque es bastante oscuro."

#. [message]
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\29_Black_Forest.cfg:442
msgid "This is the Black Forest. As you realized, it is well named."
msgstr "Este es el Bosque Negro. Como te diste cuenta, lleva bien su nombre."

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\29_Black_Forest.cfg:446
msgid ""
"Well, it seems we have to cross it to reach the Eastern Swamp and find "
"Teumiuxe's staff."
msgstr ""
"Bueno, parece que tenemos que cruzarlo para llegar al Pantano del Este y "
"encontrar el bastón de Teumiuxe."

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\29_Black_Forest.cfg:450
msgid "Please, everyone, be careful and don't get lost in the woods."
msgstr "Por favor, todos, tengan cuidado y no se pierdan en el bosque."

#. [message], speaker=second_unit
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\29_Black_Forest.cfg:467
msgid ""
"I saw something moving in the woods. It looks like some kind of huge boar "
"with glowing red eyes."
msgstr ""
"Vi algo moviéndose en el bosque. Parece una especie de jabalí enorme con "
"ojos rojos brillantes."

#. [message]
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\29_Black_Forest.cfg:471
msgid "It must be a Hell Boar."
msgstr "Debe ser un Jabalí Infernal."

#. [message]
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\29_Black_Forest.cfg:475
msgid ""
"It is said they were bread by the Ocks to be used as yoke for their wagons. "
"When they disappeared, they went free and established in the Black Forest."
msgstr ""
"Se dice que fueron criados por los Ocks para usarlos como yugo en sus "
"carretas. Cuando desaparecieron, se liberaron y se establecieron en el "
"Bosque Negro."

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\29_Black_Forest.cfg:479
msgid ""
"Be careful everyone. Remember that boars are omnivorous, which means it "
"could try to use you as a snack."
msgstr ""
"Cuidado todos. Recuerden que los jabalíes son omnívoros, lo que significa "
"que podría intentar usarlos como bocadillo."

#. [message], speaker=second_unit
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\29_Black_Forest.cfg:497
msgid "There is a huge troll here."
msgstr "Hay un troll enorme aquí."

#. [message]
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\29_Black_Forest.cfg:501
msgid ""
"This must be what's left of the vanguard. If we deal with them, we will be "
"done with the trolls that escaped the cave."
msgstr ""
"Esto debe ser lo que queda de la vanguardia. Si nos ocupamos de ellos, "
"habremos terminado con los trolls que escaparon de la cueva."

#. [message], speaker=narrator
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\29_Black_Forest.cfg:519
msgid "South: Eastern Swamp"
msgstr "Sur: Pantano Oriental"

#. [message], speaker=second_unit
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\29_Black_Forest.cfg:539
msgid "That's it. It must've been the last one."
msgstr "Listo. Debe haber sido el último."

#. [message]
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\29_Black_Forest.cfg:543
msgid ""
"This is a good thing. Trolls are already a pain in the cave, we don't want "
"them outside of it."
msgstr ""
"Esto es bueno. Los trolls ya son un dolor en la cueva, no queremos que estén "
"afuera también."

#. [message], speaker=unit
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\29_Black_Forest.cfg:564
msgid "I can see the bandits' camp from here."
msgstr "Puedo ver el campamento de los bandidos desde aquí."

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\29_Black_Forest.cfg:568
msgid "Everyone, be quiet. We will try to pass without them spotting us."
msgstr "Todos, silencio. Intentaremos pasar sin que nos vean."

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\29_Black_Forest.cfg:585
msgid ""
"At least we dealt with the trolls before fighting the bandits. We don't want "
"to fear being attacked from behind."
msgstr ""
"Al menos nos ocupamos de los trolls antes de pelear con los bandidos. No "
"queremos temer un ataque por la espalda."

#. [message], speaker=narrator
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\29_Black_Forest.cfg:612
#: .\scenarios\chapter6\41_Sand_River.cfg:830
msgid "Wheeee!"
msgstr "¡Wheeee!"

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\29_Black_Forest.cfg:616
#: .\scenarios\chapter6\41_Sand_River.cfg:834
msgid "Aaahhh!"
msgstr "¡Aaahhh!"

#. [message], speaker=narrator
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\29_Black_Forest.cfg:620
msgid "You were eaten by a Hell Boar."
msgstr "Fuiste devorado por un Jabalí Infernal."

#. [scenario], id=30_Bandit_Camp
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\30_Bandit_Camp.cfg:4
msgid "Bandit Camp"
msgstr "Campamento de Bandidos"

#. [objective], condition=win
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\30_Bandit_Camp.cfg:51
msgid "Avoid the bandits to continue west"
msgstr "Evita a los bandidos para continuar al oeste"

#. [objective], condition=win
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\30_Bandit_Camp.cfg:56
msgid "Defeat the bandit leader"
msgstr "Derrota al líder bandido"

#. [message], speaker=narrator
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\30_Bandit_Camp.cfg:403
msgid "Alas."
msgstr "Ay."

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\30_Bandit_Camp.cfg:410
msgid "They spotted us."
msgstr "Nos vieron."

#. [message]
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\30_Bandit_Camp.cfg:414
msgid ""
"This looks like a forward camp. It must be there for this exact purpose: "
"spotting travelers and calling troops to capture or kill them."
msgstr ""
"Esto parece un campamento avanzado. Debe estar ahí exactamente para eso: "
"detectar viajeros y llamar tropas para capturarlos o matarlos."

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\30_Bandit_Camp.cfg:418
msgid "I don't think we can pass undetected now..."
msgstr "No creo que podamos pasar desapercibidos ahora..."

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\30_Bandit_Camp.cfg:422
msgid "But we can still try to get across faster than their troops arrive."
msgstr ""
"Pero todavía podemos intentar cruzar más rápido de lo que lleguen sus tropas."

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\30_Bandit_Camp.cfg:426
msgid ""
"Or we try to help the Travelers and we fight them and defeat their leader."
msgstr ""
"O intentamos ayudar a los Viajeros y les peleamos y derrotamos a su líder."

#. [message], speaker=second_unit
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\30_Bandit_Camp.cfg:491
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\30_Bandit_Camp.cfg:524
msgid "That's it! We defeated the bandit leader!"
msgstr "¡Listo! ¡Derrotamos al líder de los bandidos!"

#. [message], speaker=insecond
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\30_Bandit_Camp.cfg:499
msgid "In your dream..."
msgstr "En tus sueños..."

#. [message], speaker=insecond
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\30_Bandit_Camp.cfg:503
msgid "I was only a decay. You will never find our leader."
msgstr "Solo era un desecho. Nunca encontrarán a nuestro líder."

#. [message]
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\30_Bandit_Camp.cfg:509
msgid "I am afraid he was only the second-in-command."
msgstr "Me temo que solo era el segundo al mando."

#. [message]
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\30_Bandit_Camp.cfg:513
msgid "The true leader must be hiding somewhere."
msgstr "El verdadero líder debe estar escondido en alguna parte."

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\30_Bandit_Camp.cfg:542
msgid "Let's have a look at the chests before leaving"
msgstr "Veamos los cofres antes de irnos"

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\30_Bandit_Camp.cfg:558
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\30_Bandit_Camp.cfg:580
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\30_Bandit_Camp.cfg:602
msgid "There was something in the chest."
msgstr "Había algo en el cofre."

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\30_Bandit_Camp.cfg:614
msgid "It looks like they had gathered quite a treasure."
msgstr "Parece que habían reunido bastante tesoro."

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\30_Bandit_Camp.cfg:618
msgid ""
"Now, let's continue to the Eastern Swamp. We need to find Teumiuxe's staff "
"before something worse happens."
msgstr ""
"Ahora, sigamos hacia el Pantano del Este. Tenemos que encontrar el bastón de "
"Teumiuxe antes de que pase algo peor."

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\30_Bandit_Camp.cfg:643
msgid ""
"I'm a bit sorry that we are leaving the Travelers at the mercy of the "
"bandits, but we have to find Teumiuxe's staff as soon as possible."
msgstr ""
"Lo siento un poco por dejar a los Viajeros a merced de los bandidos, pero "
"tenemos que encontrar el bastón de Teumiuxe lo antes posible."

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\30_Bandit_Camp.cfg:647
msgid "Let's continue to the Eastern Swamp."
msgstr "Sigamos hacia el Pantano del Este."

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\30_Bandit_Camp.cfg:671
msgid "Bandits... there are too many of them..."
msgstr "Bandidos... hay demasiados..."

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\30_Bandit_Camp.cfg:675
msgid "We would need an army to be able to cross."
msgstr "Necesitaríamos un ejército para poder cruzar."

#. [message], speaker=unit
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\31_Corrupted_Temple.cfg:25
msgid "Haaa! There was a huge serpent hidden in the mud."
msgstr "¡Haaa! ¡Había una serpiente enorme escondida en el barro!"

#. [scenario], id=31_Corrupted_Temple
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\31_Corrupted_Temple.cfg:34
msgid "Corrupted Temple"
msgstr "Templo Corrompido"

#. [objective], condition=win
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\31_Corrupted_Temple.cfg:68
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\32_Eastern_Swamp.cfg:38
msgid "Find the goblin's lair"
msgstr "Encuentra el escondite del goblin"

#. [objective], condition=win
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\31_Corrupted_Temple.cfg:73
msgid "Purify the temple"
msgstr "Purifica el templo"

#. [side], type=Necromancer
#. [side], type=Dark Sorcerer
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\31_Corrupted_Temple.cfg:1126
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\32_Eastern_Swamp.cfg:100
msgid "Witches"
msgstr "Brujas"

#. [side], type=White Mage
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\31_Corrupted_Temple.cfg:1277
msgid "Ofites"
msgstr "Ofitas"

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\31_Corrupted_Temple.cfg:1358
msgid "What's that smell?"
msgstr "¿Qué es ese olor?"

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\31_Corrupted_Temple.cfg:1362
msgid "THE SWAMP! IT'S THE SWAMP! WE'RE FINALLY THERE!"
msgstr "¡EL PANTANO! ¡ES EL PANTANO! ¡POR FIN LLEGAMOS!"

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\31_Corrupted_Temple.cfg:1366
msgid "I thought we never gonna get out of this dark forest."
msgstr "Pensé que nunca íbamos a salir de este bosque oscuro."

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\31_Corrupted_Temple.cfg:1370
msgid ""
"Now, we need to find where the goblin's hiding. I wonder how hard it can be."
msgstr ""
"Ahora tenemos que encontrar dónde se esconde el goblin. Me pregunto qué tan "
"difícil puede ser."

#. [message]
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\31_Corrupted_Temple.cfg:1378
msgid ""
"Well, I never heard about a goblin living in this swamp. So, he's either "
"hiding well or don't actually live there. Let's hope for the first one."
msgstr ""
"Bueno, nunca escuché de un goblin viviendo en este pantano. Así que o se "
"esconde muy bien o en realidad no vive aquí. Esperemos que sea lo primero."

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\31_Corrupted_Temple.cfg:1382
msgid "Is it more bandits I see here?"
msgstr "¿Son más bandidos los que veo aquí?"

#. [message]
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\31_Corrupted_Temple.cfg:1386
msgid ""
"Yes but it's nothing to worry about. It's most probably their second forward "
"camp, on the other side of the forest. There shouldn't be too many bandits "
"there, and they won't follow us into the swamp."
msgstr ""
"Sí, pero no hay nada de qué preocuparse. Es muy probablemente su segundo "
"campamento avanzado, al otro lado del bosque. No debería haber demasiados "
"bandidos ahí, y no nos seguirán al pantano."

#. [message], speaker=narrator
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\31_Corrupted_Temple.cfg:1406
msgid ""
"South: The Scavenger's Trading Post\n"
"North-east: Black Forest"
msgstr ""
"Sur: Puesto Comercial del Carroñero\n"
"Noreste: Bosque Negro"

#. [message], speaker=second_unit
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\31_Corrupted_Temple.cfg:1431
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\35_Scavengers_Trading_Post.cfg:2027
msgid "The tree. It's attacking me."
msgstr "El árbol. ¡Me está atacando!"

#. [message]
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\31_Corrupted_Temple.cfg:1435
msgid "It is no tree. It is a wose."
msgstr "No es un árbol. Es un wose."

#. [message]
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\31_Corrupted_Temple.cfg:1439
msgid "It looks like it was corrupted too. That's why it is attacking us."
msgstr "Parece que también está corrompido. Por eso nos está atacando."

#. [message], speaker=Io
#. [message], speaker=second_unit
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\31_Corrupted_Temple.cfg:1462
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\31_Corrupted_Temple.cfg:1472
msgid "Trolls! Again?!"
msgstr "¡Trolls! ¿Otra vez?!"

#. [message], speaker=Io
#. [message], speaker=second_unit
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\31_Corrupted_Temple.cfg:1466
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\31_Corrupted_Temple.cfg:1476
msgid "I thought we left them behind us."
msgstr "Pensé que los habíamos dejado atrás."

#. [message]
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\31_Corrupted_Temple.cfg:1486
msgid "Those are not the same."
msgstr "Estos no son los mismos."

#. [message]
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\31_Corrupted_Temple.cfg:1490
msgid ""
"The ones we left behind where cave trolls. These ones have always lived "
"here. "
msgstr ""
"Los que dejamos atrás eran trolls de cueva. Estos siempre han vivido aquí."

#. [message]
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\31_Corrupted_Temple.cfg:1494
msgid ""
"There are not many of them, but they can be dangerous to travelers anyway."
msgstr ""
"No hay muchos, pero de todos modos pueden ser peligrosos para los viajeros."

#. [message], speaker=second_unit
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\31_Corrupted_Temple.cfg:1592
msgid "The guardian is dead. We should be able to purify the temple now."
msgstr "El guardián está muerto. Ahora deberíamos poder purificar el templo."

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\31_Corrupted_Temple.cfg:1597
msgid "We need to find the altar, and place the artifact on it."
msgstr "Tenemos que encontrar el altar y colocar el artefacto ahí."

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\31_Corrupted_Temple.cfg:1616
msgid "We first need to defeat the guardian to purify the temple."
msgstr "Primero tenemos que derrotar al guardián para purificar el templo."

#. [message], speaker=unit
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\31_Corrupted_Temple.cfg:1625
msgid "That's it, the temple is purified."
msgstr "Listo, el templo está purificado."

#. [message], speaker=unit
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\31_Corrupted_Temple.cfg:1632
msgid ""
"The front of the altar opened when I placed the artifact on it. There is a "
"treasure in it. "
msgstr ""
"La parte frontal del altar se abrió cuando coloqué el artefacto. Hay un "
"tesoro dentro."

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\31_Corrupted_Temple.cfg:1636
msgid "This might be useful for our journey."
msgstr "Esto podría ser útil para nuestro viaje."

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\31_Corrupted_Temple.cfg:1640
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\31_Corrupted_Temple.cfg:1670
msgid ""
"It looks like the goblin is not in this part of the swamp. Let's go further "
"in."
msgstr ""
"Parece que el goblin no está en esta parte del pantano. Sigamos más adentro."

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\31_Corrupted_Temple.cfg:1644
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\31_Corrupted_Temple.cfg:1674
msgid "<i>To himself</i> I hope he is indeed in the swamp."
msgstr "<i>Para sí mismo</i> Espero que realmente esté en el pantano."

#. [message], speaker=unit
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\31_Corrupted_Temple.cfg:1704
msgid "You look badly hurt. What happened to you?"
msgstr "Estás muy malherido. ¿Qué te pasó?"

#. [message], speaker=ofite
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\31_Corrupted_Temple.cfg:1708
msgid "<i>dying</i> I am of no importance, only the temple is."
msgstr "<i>muriendo</i> Yo no tengo importancia, solo el templo la tiene."

#. [message], speaker=ofite
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\31_Corrupted_Temple.cfg:1712
msgid "Please, the temple must be purified. The evil grows stronger every day."
msgstr ""
"Por favor, el templo debe ser purificado. El mal crece más fuerte cada día."

#. [message], speaker=ofite
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\31_Corrupted_Temple.cfg:1716
msgid ""
"Take this idol. The temple is in thrall to a malevolent spirit. The idol can "
"break the curse if you place it on the altar."
msgstr ""
"Toma este ídolo. El templo está esclavizado por un espíritu malévolo. El "
"ídolo puede romper la maldición si lo colocas en el altar."

#. [message], speaker=ofite
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\31_Corrupted_Temple.cfg:1720
msgid ""
"I tried once in vain. The presence of a powerful guardian is synonymous with "
"desecration. Please, you must… <i>dies</i>"
msgstr ""
"Lo intenté una vez en vano. La presencia de un guardián poderoso es sinónimo "
"de profanación. Por favor, ustedes deben… <i>muere</i>"

#. [message], speaker=unit
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\31_Corrupted_Temple.cfg:1729
msgid "Poor man."
msgstr "Pobre hombre."

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\31_Corrupted_Temple.cfg:1733
msgid ""
"He didn't even tell us where the temple is. I guess we will figure out when "
"we find it."
msgstr ""
"Ni siquiera nos dijo dónde está el templo. Supongo que lo averiguaremos "
"cuando lo encontremos."

#. [message], speaker=narrator
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\31_Corrupted_Temple.cfg:1773
msgid "Glorp"
msgstr "Glorp"

#. [message]
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\31_Corrupted_Temple.cfg:1777
msgid "Oh no! He fell into a pothole."
msgstr "¡Oh no! ¡Se cayó en un hoyo!"

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\31_Corrupted_Temple.cfg:1783
msgid ""
"These summoners... they are spawning creatures faster than we can kill them. "
"We need to find another way into the swamp."
msgstr ""
"Estos invocadores... están generando criaturas más rápido de lo que podemos "
"matarlas. Necesitamos encontrar otra forma de entrar al pantano."

#. [message], speaker=second_unit
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\31_Corrupted_Temple.cfg:1802
msgid "Weird. These looks exactly like the previous one we killed."
msgstr "Qué raro. Este se ve exactamente igual que el anterior que matamos."

#. [message], speaker=second_unit
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\31_Corrupted_Temple.cfg:1809
msgid "This time, I'm sure. I already killed this one."
msgstr "Esta vez estoy seguro. Ya maté a este."

#. [message]
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\31_Corrupted_Temple.cfg:1813
msgid ""
"That's probably not a real animal. The witches there must be summoning them."
msgstr ""
"Ese probablemente no es un animal real. Las brujas de ahí deben estar "
"invocándolos."

#. [message]
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\31_Corrupted_Temple.cfg:1817
msgid ""
"Kill the witches before killing the Vine Tigers, otherwise we will never see "
"the end of it."
msgstr ""
"Matemos a las brujas antes que a los Tigres de Enredadera, de lo contrario "
"nunca veremos el final."

#. [message], speaker=unit
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\31_Corrupted_Temple.cfg:1838
msgid "Look over there! It looks like the witch had a horse."
msgstr "¡Miren allá! Parece que la bruja tenía un caballo."

#. [message], speaker=unit
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\31_Corrupted_Temple.cfg:1842
msgid "Should we take it with us?"
msgstr "¿Deberíamos llevarlo con nosotros?"

#. [option]
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\31_Corrupted_Temple.cfg:1844
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:1469
msgid "Yes, we cannot let it die here and we need one."
msgstr "Sí, no podemos dejar que muera aquí y necesitamos uno."

#. [message], speaker=unit
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\31_Corrupted_Temple.cfg:1865
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:1490
msgid ""
"I am sorry pal, but now that I think about it, I wouldn't know what to do of "
"a horse right now."
msgstr ""
"Lo siento amigo, pero ahora que lo pienso, no sabría qué hacer con un "
"caballo justo ahora."

#. [option]
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\31_Corrupted_Temple.cfg:1881
msgid "No, leave it be. I don't trust witch's horses."
msgstr "No, déjalo. No confío en caballos de brujas."

#. [message], speaker=unit
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\31_Corrupted_Temple.cfg:1897
msgid "There was a coven in the hut."
msgstr "Había un aquelarre en la cabaña."

#. [message], speaker=unit
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\31_Corrupted_Temple.cfg:1957
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\31_Corrupted_Temple.cfg:2020
msgid "There is a rusty metal door. Should I open it?"
msgstr "Hay una puerta de metal oxidada. ¿Debo abrirla?"

#. [option]
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\31_Corrupted_Temple.cfg:1959
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\31_Corrupted_Temple.cfg:1984
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\31_Corrupted_Temple.cfg:2022
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\31_Corrupted_Temple.cfg:2047
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\33_Goblins_Lair.cfg:1780
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\33_Goblins_Lair.cfg:1883
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\33_Goblins_Lair.cfg:2094
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\33_Goblins_Lair.cfg:2137
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\33_Goblins_Lair.cfg:2180
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\33_Goblins_Lair.cfg:2223
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\33_Goblins_Lair.cfg:2266
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\33_Goblins_Lair.cfg:2393
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\33_Goblins_Lair.cfg:2436
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\34_Hive.cfg:1330 .\scenarios\chapter4\34_Hive.cfg:1373
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\34_Hive.cfg:1416 .\scenarios\chapter4\34_Hive.cfg:1459
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\34_Hive.cfg:1502 .\scenarios\chapter4\34_Hive.cfg:1549
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\34_Hive.cfg:1691
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:1008
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:1051
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:1094
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:1137
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:1180
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:1228
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:1295
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:1351
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:1407
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:1532
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:1575
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:1617
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:1669
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:1709
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:1738
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:1888
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:1924
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:1960
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:1996
msgid "Yes, please."
msgstr "Sí, por favor."

#. [message], speaker=unit
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\31_Corrupted_Temple.cfg:1982
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\31_Corrupted_Temple.cfg:2045
msgid "There is a rusty metal door. Should I close it?"
msgstr "Hay una puerta de metal oxidada. ¿Debo cerrarla?"

#. [scenario], id=32_Eastern_Swamp
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\32_Eastern_Swamp.cfg:4
msgid "Eastern Swamp"
msgstr "Pantano Oriental"

#. [side], type=Troll Warrior
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\32_Eastern_Swamp.cfg:82
msgid "Swamp Trolls"
msgstr "Trolls del Pantano"

#. [side], type=Gobot Scorcher LoI
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\32_Eastern_Swamp.cfg:829
msgid "Gobots"
msgstr "Gobots"

#. [side]
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\32_Eastern_Swamp.cfg:846
msgid "Allies"
msgstr "Aliados"

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\32_Eastern_Swamp.cfg:901
msgid ""
"Well, it's the last part of the swamp we have not searched. If we do not "
"find the goblin's lair here, we will have to go back..."
msgstr ""
"Bueno, es la última parte del pantano que no hemos buscado. Si no "
"encontramos la guarida del goblin aquí, tendremos que volver..."

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\32_Eastern_Swamp.cfg:905
msgid ""
"If anyone notices anything out of place in this swamp, tell us. That might "
"be the hint we are looking for."
msgstr ""
"Si alguien nota algo fuera de lugar en este pantano, avísennos. Eso podría "
"ser la pista que estamos buscando."

#. [message], speaker=narrator
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\32_Eastern_Swamp.cfg:920
msgid "Potions"
msgstr "Pociones"

#. [message], speaker=unit
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\32_Eastern_Swamp.cfg:945
msgid "Aaaahhhh!!!"
msgstr "¡Aaaahhhh!!!"

#. [0]
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\32_Eastern_Swamp.cfg:973
msgid ""
"We fell into a hole and into some kind of old temple. There seem to be Vine "
"Tigers."
msgstr ""
"Cayimos en un agujero y en algún tipo de templo antiguo. Parece haber Tigres "
"de Vid."

#. [message], speaker=unit
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\32_Eastern_Swamp.cfg:988
msgid "There's someone in the hut."
msgstr "Hay alguien en la cabaña."

#. [message], speaker=narrator
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\32_Eastern_Swamp.cfg:994
msgid ""
"Ah finally! I was starting to think all humans were gone. It looks like the "
"country was invaded by monsters!"
msgstr ""
"¡Ah por fin! Ya estaba empezando a pensar que todos los humanos se habían "
"ido. ¡Parece que el país fue invadido por monstruos!"

#. [message], speaker=narrator
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\32_Eastern_Swamp.cfg:1035
msgid "I'm Nrifyo, a young mage."
msgstr "Soy Nrifyo, un mago joven."

#. [message], speaker=narrator
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\32_Eastern_Swamp.cfg:1052
msgid ""
"I arrived here following the trail of the gold pinched during Eukhac’s "
"bowman tournament."
msgstr ""
"Llegué aquí siguiendo el rastro del oro robado durante el torneo de arqueros "
"de Eukhac."

#. [message], speaker=narrator
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\32_Eastern_Swamp.cfg:1079
msgid ""
"Listen, I know I am young for a mage, but I know one or two spells and I’m "
"ready to help you for a decent price. Let's say, 49000 gold."
msgstr ""
"Escucha, sé que soy joven para un mago, pero conozco uno o dos hechizos y "
"estoy listo para ayudarte por un precio decente. Digamos, 49000 oro."

#. [message], speaker=narrator
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\32_Eastern_Swamp.cfg:1085
msgid "Honestly, I know my job! I only need someone to watch my back."
msgstr ""
"¡Honestamente, conozco mi trabajo! Solo necesito a alguien que me cubra las "
"espaldas."

#. [option]
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\32_Eastern_Swamp.cfg:1087
msgid "We would be glad to have you with us."
msgstr "Nos alegraría tenerte con nosotros."

#. [message], speaker=narrator
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\32_Eastern_Swamp.cfg:1099
msgid "I am afraid you don't have enough gold to hire me."
msgstr "Temo que no tienes suficiente oro para contratarme."

#. [message], speaker=Nrifyo
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\32_Eastern_Swamp.cfg:1150
msgid ""
"By the stars, could have my luck changed? Nrifyo, mage apprentice, at your "
"service!"
msgstr ""
"¡Por las estrellas, podría haber cambiado mi suerte? ¡Nrifyo, aprendiz de "
"mago, a tu servicio!"

#. [message], speaker=narrator
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\32_Eastern_Swamp.cfg:1170
msgid "Well… Yes, it was to be expected!"
msgstr "Bueno… ¡Sí, era de esperarse!"

#. [message], speaker=narrator
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\32_Eastern_Swamp.cfg:1176
msgid ""
"I can’t see straight anymore, with all the hits my poor nut received, "
"lately. See you around."
msgstr ""
"No puedo ver derecho ya, con todos los golpes que mi pobre cabeza recibió "
"últimamente. Nos vemos."

#. [message], speaker=unit
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\32_Eastern_Swamp.cfg:1209
msgid "There's a witch in the hut."
msgstr "Hay una bruja en la cabaña."

#. [message], speaker=trader
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\32_Eastern_Swamp.cfg:1220
msgid "Come in, come in! I won't hurt you."
msgstr "¡Pasen, pasen! No les haré daño."

#. [message], speaker=trader
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\32_Eastern_Swamp.cfg:1224
msgid ""
"Oooh! Look at these beautiful men. Ain’t they magnificent in their suits? "
msgstr ""
"¡Ooooh! Miren a estos hermosos hombres. ¿No son magníficos con sus trajes?"

#. [message], speaker=trader
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\32_Eastern_Swamp.cfg:1228
msgid "Admire their proud air. Their look neither bat nor falter. "
msgstr "Admiren su aire orgulloso. Su mirada ni pestañea ni titubea."

#. [message], speaker=trader
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\32_Eastern_Swamp.cfg:1232
msgid ""
"But Meixmi knows how to catch their attention. She has a profusion of "
"curative balms. "
msgstr ""
"Pero Meixmi sabe cómo captar su atención. Tiene una profusión de bálsamos "
"curativos."

#. [message], speaker=trader
#: .\scenarios\chapter4\32_Eastern_Swamp.cfg:1273
msgid ""
"My potions are coming out of the caldron. Against a few coins, they will "
"heal you."
msgstr ""
"Mis pociones están saliendo del caldero. Por unas pocas monedas, te sanarán."

