#. [object]
#: .\utils\item_list.cfg:3596
msgid "Life of Uteaqniq Zei"
msgstr "Vida de Uteaqniq Zei"

#. [object]
#: .\utils\item_list.cfg:3601
msgid ""
"Uteaqniq Zei knew everything about business. After a miserable childhood in "
"the streets of the imperial capital of Wesnoth, he spent most of his teenage "
"years transforming stolen eggs or smashed glass into warm meals.\n"
"\n"
"During a brief mission in the 2nd legion, he learnt to trade and mastered "
"the art of finding terrific deals. But the gloom of military life was "
"incompatible with his desire of adventure. He therefore resigned to join a "
"small trading company in the west.\n"
"\n"
"Sometime after arriving at Idaamub, Zei met the Dunefolks. He quickly became "
"aware that they had more to offer than exotic weapons and jewels that other "
"companies could not buy. By chance, he had seen the Dunefolks manipulating "
"materials looking like eggshells, thick as a human hand and shining "
"splendidly. Judging by the way they were bending them, Zei estimated they "
"were harder than granite. If he could get enough of them to pave the floor "
"of the house of some fortunate patrician, he would earn quite a sum. \n"
"\n"
"Fortunately for Zei, the shells were worthless to the Dunefolks, who were "
"happy to get rid of them. Their joy doubled when Zei offered them in "
"exchange the same objects many companies had offered them in exchange for "
"their weapons and jewels. \n"
"\n"
"With time, the Dunefolks made Uteaqniq one of their privileged associates, "
"and even went as far as giving him some weapons, despite having refused "
"other interested partners. Uteaqniq’s wealth never stopped growing during "
"those time, and at the time of the punishment of Dunefolks, he had become "
"one of the most fortunate citizens of Idaamub."
msgstr ""
"Uteaqniq Zei sabía todo sobre los negocios. Tras una infancia miserable en "
"las calles de la capital imperial de Wesnoth, pasó la mayor parte de su "
"adolescencia transformando huevos robados o vidrio roto en comidas "
"calientes.\n"
"\n"
"Durante una breve misión en la 2.ª legión, aprendió a comerciar y dominó el "
"arte de encontrar ofertas excelentes. Pero la dureza de la vida militar era "
"incompatible con su deseo de aventura. Por eso renunció y se unió a una "
"pequeña compañía comercial en el oeste.\n"
"\n"
"Algún tiempo después de llegar a Idaamub, Zei conoció a los Barjanes. "
"Rápidamente se dio cuenta de que tenían mucho más que ofrecer que armas "
"exóticas y joyas que otras compañías no podían comprar. Por casualidad, "
"había visto a los Barjanes manipular materiales que parecían cáscaras de "
"huevo, gruesas como una mano humana y con un brillo espléndido. Por la forma "
"en que las doblaban, Zei estimó que eran más duras que el granito. Si "
"lograba conseguir suficientes para pavimentar el suelo de la casa de algún "
"patricio afortunado, ganaría una buena suma.\n"
"\n"
"Afortunadamente para Zei, las cáscaras no tenían valor para los Barjanes, "
"que estaban contentos de deshacerse de ellas. Su alegría se duplicó cuando "
"Zei les ofreció a cambio los mismos objetos que muchas compañías les habían "
"ofrecido por sus armas y joyas.\n"
"\n"
"Con el tiempo, los Barjanes hicieron de Uteaqniq uno de sus socios "
"privilegiados e incluso le dieron algunas armas, a pesar de haber rechazado "
"a otros interesados. La riqueza de Uteaqniq no dejó de crecer durante ese "
"tiempo y, cuando llegó el castigo de los Barjanes, ya se había convertido en "
"uno de los ciudadanos más afortunados de Idaamub."

