#. [object]
#: .\utils\item_list.cfg:4545
msgid "History of the Dunefolks"
msgstr "Historia de los Barjanes"

#. [object]
#: .\utils\item_list.cfg:4550
msgid ""
"A long time ago, a company of imperial merchants looking for new routes to "
"the other side of the Green Mountains were surprised to discover a huge "
"community living in the Fire Cliffs.\n"
"\n"
"The impressive weapons and jewels possessed by those humble troglodytes were "
"beyond belief but the Dunefolks, self-sufficient, saw no reason to trade "
"items of value against the trinkets that were offering the imperial "
"merchants.\n"
"\n"
"During the following years, the merchants vainly tried to convince the "
"Dunefolks, until a company presented them a roll of shimmering fabric "
"brought, with other goods, from the imperial capital city. The Dunefolks "
"were immediately bewitched by the presented model and gladly agreed to sell "
"some of their best weapons to the astonished merchants.\n"
"\n"
"With their eyes full of golden images, the caravan rushed back to the "
"capital city and, once back, prepared in the highest secret, loads of "
"fabrics to barter with the Dunefolks. Unfortunately for them, the capital "
"city and the Dunefolks were connected by a 730-league-long dangerous "
"commercial route, often scene of goblin attacks.\n"
"\n"
"Fate then decided the caravan to be captured and the goblin to learn the "
"interest of the Dunefolks to the fabrics of their prisoners. Goblins had "
"given up trading with the Dunefolks centuries before and diligent goblins "
"therefore assessed the loots.\n"
"\n"
"In six months, the small group of goblins evaded on numerous occasions "
"Legion patrols and carried many rolls of fabrics but arriving at the Fire "
"Cliffs, they realized they had been outstripped by an independent merchant "
"named Uteaqniq Zei. The Dunefolks were still interested in goblin’s goods "
"but, because of the commercial relation tied with Uteaqniq, were not willing "
"to batter them against their items anymore. Goblins were forced to retreat "
"with a trivial quantity of baskets, incomplete necklaces, and cast-off "
"mining tools in exchange for their goods formerly so precious.\n"
"\n"
"Goblins never forgot Uteaqniq Zei and decided that, many years later, they "
"would have their revenge."
msgstr ""
"Hace mucho tiempo, una compañía de mercaderes imperiales que buscaba nuevas "
"rutas hacia el otro lado de las Montañas Verdes se sorprendió al descubrir "
"una enorme comunidad viviendo en los Acantilados de Fuego.\n"
"\n"
"Las impresionantes armas y joyas que poseían esos humildes trogloditas eran "
"increíbles, pero los barjanes, autosuficientes, no veían razón para "
"intercambiar objetos de valor por las baratijas que ofrecían los mercaderes "
"imperiales.\n"
"\n"
"Durante los años siguientes, los mercaderes intentaron en vano convencer a "
"los barjanes, hasta que una compañía les presentó un rollo de tela brillante "
"traído, junto con otros bienes, desde la capital imperial. Los barjanes "
"quedaron inmediatamente fascinados por el modelo presentado y aceptaron con "
"gusto vender algunas de sus mejores armas a los mercaderes sorprendidos.\n"
"\n"
"Con los ojos llenos de imágenes doradas, la caravana regresó apresuradamente "
"a la capital y, una vez allí, preparó en el mayor secreto grandes cantidades "
"de telas para intercambiar con los barjanes. Desafortunadamente para ellos, "
"la capital y los barjanes estaban conectados por una peligrosa ruta "
"comercial de 730 leguas, a menudo escenario de ataques goblins.\n"
"\n"
"El destino quiso que la caravana fuera capturada y que los goblins "
"descubrieran el interés de los barjanes por las telas de sus prisioneros. "
"Los goblins habían dejado de comerciar con los barjanes siglos antes, por lo "
"que evaluaron cuidadosamente el botín.\n"
"\n"
"En seis meses, el pequeño grupo de goblins evitó en numerosas ocasiones las "
"patrullas de la Legión y transportó muchos rollos de tela, pero al llegar a "
"los Acantilados de Fuego se dieron cuenta de que habían sido superados por "
"un mercader independiente llamado Uteaqniq Zei. Los barjanes seguían "
"interesados en los bienes de los goblins, pero debido a la relación "
"comercial con Uteaqniq, ya no estaban dispuestos a intercambiarlos por sus "
"objetos. Los goblins se vieron obligados a retirarse con una cantidad "
"insignificante de cestas, collares incompletos y herramientas de minería "
"desechadas a cambio de sus bienes antes tan valiosos.\n"
"\n"
"Los goblins nunca olvidaron a Uteaqniq Zei y decidieron que, muchos años "
"después, tendrían su venganza."

#. [object]
#: .\utils\item_list.cfg:4565
msgid "From swords to shares"
msgstr "De espadas a acciones"

#. [object]
#: .\utils\item_list.cfg:4570
msgid ""
"Hcui Loazfa was carrying the torch of his beloved 10th Legion for twenty "
"years already. Under his command, the Legion had become one of the most "
"talented military unit of all time, coming through the challenge of the "
"pacification of Xvaenc’s peninsula and the War of Legions with minor "
"losses.\n"
"\n"
"But having vanquished, to some exceptions, its most famous enemies, the "
"Legion suddenly fell into an identity crisis. The empire to which it had "
"sworn allegiance was not anymore and the quarrels in its ranks were more "
"numerous than ever. ''Nothing is more terrible than an army with no enemy to "
"fight.'', noted then down a frustrated Loazfa in his chronicles. ''I have "
"seen enough blood in my life, and I could satisfy myself with an acre of "
"land, a spade and mule for the rest of my life but what will I do with all "
"this enthusiastic young people?''\n"
"\n"
"The first day of the new year, talking to an assembly of chilled-to-the-bone "
"worried men, Hcui Loazfa announced that the 10th Legion would not be able to "
"subsist like that. Food was short, especially because of too few farmers and "
"too many legionnaires. He then offered his men bet on good fortune and start "
"back from zero and create a new kingdom.\n"
"\n"
"Immediately, Loafza was asked to take the throne of Idaamub but he "
"gracefully declined the offer, arguing that the new kingdom will need an "
"army and that it was his intentions to guide it through the difficult times "
"awaiting. Refugees from other regions were already flocking, trying to "
"protect themselves from the chaos that was raging in Sob Plain. But he was "
"suspecting other visitors, this time less benevolent, will soon join them as "
"soon as the news of Idaamub’s good fortune will spread."
msgstr ""
"Hcui Loazfa llevaba ya veinte años portando la antorcha de su querida 10.ª "
"Legión. Bajo su mando, la Legión se había convertido en una de las unidades "
"militares más talentosas de todos los tiempos, superando la pacificación de "
"la península de Xvaenc y la Guerra de las Legiones con pérdidas mínimas.\n"
"\n"
"Pero tras haber derrotado, con pocas excepciones, a sus enemigos más "
"famosos, la Legión cayó de repente en una crisis de identidad. El imperio al "
"que había jurado lealtad ya no existía y los conflictos en sus filas eran "
"más numerosos que nunca. «Nada es más terrible que un ejército sin enemigo "
"al que combatir», anotó un frustrado Loazfa en sus crónicas. «He visto "
"suficiente sangre en mi vida, y podría conformarme con un terreno, una pala "
"y una mula por el resto de mis días, pero ¿qué haré con toda esta gente "
"joven entusiasta?»\n"
"\n"
"El primer día del año nuevo, hablando ante una asamblea de hombres "
"preocupados y helados hasta los huesos, Hcui Loazfa anunció que la 10.ª "
"Legión no podría seguir así. La comida escaseaba, especialmente porque había "
"muy pocos agricultores y demasiados legionarios. Entonces propuso apostar "
"por la buena fortuna, empezar desde cero y crear un nuevo reino.\n"
"\n"
"Inmediatamente le pidieron a Loazfa que tomara el trono de Idaamub, pero él "
"rechazó la oferta con elegancia, argumentando que el nuevo reino necesitaría "
"un ejército y que su intención era guiarlo a través de los tiempos difíciles "
"que se avecinaban. Refugiados de otras regiones ya estaban llegando en masa, "
"buscando protegerse del caos que asolaba la Llanura de Sob. Pero sospechaba "
"que pronto llegarían otros visitantes, esta vez menos benevolentes, en "
"cuanto se difundiera la noticia de la buena fortuna de Idaamub."

